Lin2 bat chiah8 kam-chia3 bo5?  Kam-chia3 si7 tiN e5, a2-si7 khou2 e5?  Kam-chia3 oe7 thang choe3 sim2-mih8?  Lan2 teh chiah8 e5 thng5 si7 eng7 kam-chia3 choe3 e5, m7-ku2 u7 e5 sou2-chai7 bo5 chhut kam-chia3, sou2-i2 hia e5 lang5 long2 m7-bat chiah8 ke3 kam-chia3.
U7 chit8 pai2, Sun5-sun5 kap ma-ma khi3 Jit8-pun2, in boe2 chit8 chat kam-chia3 theh8 khi3 Jit8-pun2, ti7 Jit8-pun2 u7 chin choe7 gin2-na2 ui5 oa2 lai5 khoaN3 Sun5-sun5 chhiu2 nih8 e5 kam-chia3, in-ui7 in long2 m7-bat khoaN3-ke3 kam-chia3.  
Hiah e5 gin2-na2 ti7 piN-a2 chhai-lai5 chhai-khi3, u7 e5 kong2: “Si7 chit8 ki koaiN2-a2.”  U7 e5 kong2: “Si7 chit8 ki ang5 tek ko.”  Ia2 u7 lang5 kong2: “Si7 chit8 ki kun3-a2.”  Ki5-tiong u7 chit8 e5 toa7-siaN hoah kong2: “Goa2 chai, che si7 chit8-ki kam-chia3.”  Goan5-lai5 chit e5 gin2-na2 ti7 teng2 geh8-jit8 kap pa-pa chiah tui3 Tai5-oan5 tng2-lai5, i bat chiah8, sou2-i2 i ioh tioh8 lah.  
Se3-kan lang5 tai7-pou7 hun7 long2 m7-bat Ia5-sou, sou2-i2 ou-peh8-ioh, chhin-chhiuN7 hiah e5 m7-chai-iaN2 kam-chia3 e5 gin2-na2 chit8-iuN7. 
(“Ia5-sou e5 gian5-heng5”, 1969, iah8 42 )
